I stumbled upon this deli when I first started working in the neighborhood in 2010, and I've been a loyal customer ever since... The staff are friendly and efficient, and despite the presence of lines during the height of the breakfast and lunch hours, I'm always able to get in, grab my food for takeaway, and out quickly. For those that would like to eat on-site/nearby, there is a small dining area in the deli and publically accessible outdoor courtyards that can be used during the warmer months of the year. The menu is made up of both non-rotating and rotating selections spanning from generous deli sandwiches to Korean Thursdays (I love when the kimchi, kimbap and other Korean favorites come out on Thursdays). Breakfast is also solid here--my personal favorite is the potato, egg and cheese breakfast wrap with bacon. The deli also offers a wide selection of beverages, chips, and sweet items (they usually have Austrian Manner here, and the house-baked cookies are large). 2 Sisters Deli is a solid choice for those looking for a place to eat in the neighborhood.
